Male (Pacific).description: Bushtits are smaller than Wrentits—about the size of a kinglet, whereas Wrentits are sparrow sized. Bushtits have smaller features all around: smaller bills, shorter legs, and smaller heads. Bushtits are also more active and easier to see than Wrentits.

Adult/immature.description: Oak Titmice have crests and shorter tails than Wrentits. Titmice also forage actively in trees and shrubs whereas Wrentits tend to stay hidden in shrubs.
